dod-rio pack — content licence
===============================

This pack is derived from:
    DoD Risk, Issue, and Opportunity Management Guide for Defense Acquisition Programs
    OUSD(R&E) (Office of the Under Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering)
    September 2023, Incorporating Change 2.2 (December 2023)
    Distribution Statement A: Approved for public release; distribution is unlimited.

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work); Distribution A  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the Office of the Under
Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering, and is therefore NOT subject to copyright
protection in the United States (17 U.S.C. 105). It carries Distribution Statement A (approved
for public release; distribution unlimited). It is in the public domain: anyone may reproduce,
transform, and redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially, without permission,
attribution, or share-alike obligation.

THIRD-PARTY / EXTERNAL MATERIAL CAVEAT: the guide names and references external policy,
standards, and tooling — including DoD Instructions and Directives (e.g. DoDI 5000.02/.74/.75/
.80/.81/.85/.87/.88/.89/.91, DoDI 8500.01/8510.01, DoDI 5000.83/5000.90, DoDD 5000.01),
industry and military standards (EIA-748 for EVM, MIL-STD-881F for the WBS, MIL-STD-882 for
system safety), the DCMA 14-point schedule metrics, NIST SP 800-39, and commercial/Service
tools (Active Risk Manager, Project Recon, Risk Exchange). Those artifacts remain governed by
their own authorities and licences. This pack reproduces none of them — it contains only
synthesized, transformed reference notes that NAME these artifacts and describe, in original
words, how the RIO guide uses them. No third-party standard text, tables, or long verbatim
passages are reproduced.

Attribution to OUSD(R&E) / the DoD is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a
legal obligation. The DoD does not endorse this pack or its authors.

